==Definition==

'''Woodcraft''', simply defined, in Tolkien's works refers to '''the art of survival as well as skill and experience in anything related to the woodlands.'''

The Merriam-Webster dictionary defines woodcraft as:

'''Wood-craft: /wu̇d-ˌkraft./ 1. skill and practice in anything relating to the woods and especially in maintaining oneself and making one's way in the woods.'''


